raw_data.title: Application Architect
raw_data.description: Application Architect interprets technical architecture and design of Health IT applications, coding (construction), and continuous testing of complex modules and applications in support of the TeleTracking’s cloud platform.

raw_data.title: Application Consultant (AC)
raw_data.description: The Application Consultant (AC) is responsible for developing client-specific materials to support on-site delivery activities that lead to agreed-upon client outcomes. The primary role of the AC is to conduct classroom training and configuration sessions, as well as provide go-live support for all of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. Additionally, the AC engages in concurrent data analysis throughout engagements to support both validation of client outcomes and identify opportunities for further client process and solution optimizations.

raw_data.title: Application Deployment Engineer (ADE)
raw_data.description: The Application Deployment Engineer (ADE) is responsible for the implementation of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions, and works directly with Services Technical Project Managers and Service Managers to plan and implement the technical aspects of on-premise and SaaS-based Health IT implementation projects and or services engagement. The Application Deployment Engineer works with client personnel to deploy TeleTracking solutions.

raw_data.title: Advisory Consultant (ADV)
raw_data.description: The Advisory Consultant (ADV) is responsible for executing consultative  engagements involving complex Health IT systems for integrated healthcare delivery organizations. The ADV leads change management efforts and process improvement initiatives through coordination and support of client leadership. The ADV manages relationships with senior executives in client organizations, facilitates process improvement, and targets change activities to achieve desired client outcomes through optimized workflows and advises on Health IT adoption strategy.

raw_data.title: Associate Product Designer
raw_data.description: Associate Product Designer supports a Product Designer with creating single applications based on user requirements. Works  with stakeholders to gather requirements for creating solutions on TeleTracking’s Health IT platform.

raw_data.title: Business Intelligence Analyst (BIA)
raw_data.description: The Business Intelligence Analyst (BIA) position exists to help our clients to access and interpret key performance metrics and their relationships to outcomes associated with TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. The BIA is responsible for the design, build, and associated consulting on analytics through the use of our analytics platform and other available tools.

raw_data.title: Configuration Analyst (CA)
raw_data.description: The Configuration Analyst’s (CA) main responsibility is designing and coding database configurations to deliver a operational workflow solution in procedural areas and ambulatory clinics. The Configuration Analyst is responsible for leveraging TeleTracking’s leading practices and our client’s clinical and operational workflow  to design and configure TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions.

raw_data.title: Cloud Deployment Engineer (CDE)
raw_data.description: The Cloud Deployment Engineer (CDE) is responsible for the implementation of TeleTracking’s cloud-based Health IT solutions.  The CDE works directly with Technical Project Managers and Service Managers to plan and implement the technical aspects of on-premise, SaaS-based Health IT implementation projects, and services engagements. The CDE works with client personnel to deploy TeleTracking solutions.

raw_data.title: Data Architect
raw_data.description: Data Architect leads the architecture and design of TeleTracking’s Data Platform for aggregating customer and healthcare operational data, and providing access to operational insights. This position is  responsible for the technical and security architecture of Health IT applications, as well as the supporting infrastructure. This position helps drive quality, reliable, secure applications, using Health IT industry standard best practices.

raw_data.title: Delivery Director (DD)
raw_data.description: The Delivery Director (DD) has overall responsibility for the management of all global Client Delivery teams. This position establishes the client delivery strategy for Health IT solutions, provides executive oversight, and subject matter understanding  to the Client Delivery teams, while defining processes and building organizational capabilities. The Director is a part of the leadership team and collaborates with fellow transformation leaders to streamline the delivery of Health IT services and drive both client and employee involvement.

raw_data.title: Data Engineer 1 (DE1)
raw_data.description: Data Engineer 1 (DE1) assists in the writing, debugging, unit testing, and performance test code in the data access layer of Health IT applications.

raw_data.title: Data Engineer 2 (DE2)
raw_data.description: Data Engineer 2 (DE2) participates in data modeling and completes coding of Health IT applications. Uses the software development lifecycle to configure the database. Leverages big data  technology and object-oriented design (classes, constructors, interfaces, properties, methods, and events) to capture and manage select data.

raw_data.title: Data Engineer 3 (DE3)
raw_data.description: Data Engineer 3 (DE3) leads data modeling and oversees coding activities of DE1s and DE2s. Uses the software development lifecycle to configure the database. Leverages big data technology and object-oriented design (classes, constructors, interfaces, properties, methods, and events) to capture and manage all data within Health IT applications.

raw_data.title: Development Operations Engineer 1 (DevOps 1)
raw_data.description: DevOps Engineer 1 (DevOps1) designs and implements the next generation framework for development, testing, documentation, and deployment of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. This includes the maintenance of the internal infrastructure that supports the software development, test, and documentation teams.

raw_data.title: Development Operations Engineer 2 (DevOps 2)
raw_data.description: DevOps Engineer 2 (DevOps 2) works with multiple engineering teams to help ensure that the infrastructure is available. The DevOps Engineer 2 leverages existing development and deployment pipeline to  design and implement the next generation framework for development, testing, documentation, and deployment of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. Conducts maintenance on the internal infrastructure that supports the software development, test, and documentation.

raw_data.title: Development Operations Engineer 3 (DevOps 3)
raw_data.description: DevOps Engineer 3 (DevOps 3) works with multiple engineering teams to help ensure that the infrastructure is available.  The DevOps Engineer 3 leverages existing development and deployment pipeline to  design and implement the next generation framework for development, testing, documentation, and deployment of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. Conducts maintenance on the internal infrastructure that supports the software development, test, and documentation. The position improves DevOps processes and creates new DevOps tools that support agile application development teams enables continuous integration, test, and deployment methods. The DevOps Engineer 3 assists with application integration and troubleshooting in this multi-application environment, including management of dependencies on services, platforms, and other applications.

raw_data.title: Director of Infrastructure Engineering
raw_data.description: Director of Infrastructure Engineering manages the infrastructure team responsible for Health IT Cloud infrastructure, and sets the future direction of infrastructure architecture. This includes all internal and Cloud based hosting, risk mitigation, the development of Health IT solutions in support of the application landscape, and data management. The Director of Infrastructure Engineering leads the day-to-day functions of the infrastructure team ensuring that the resources are allocated, projects are on track and on budget, and ensures that the infrastructure strategy and roadmap are aligned with Product Development and Software Engineering.

raw_data.title: Delivery Manager (DM)
raw_data.description: The Delivery Manager (DM) leads a team of Workflow Consultants and Application Consultants to help ensure successful implementation of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. The DM manages the day-to-day functions of these resources and is a subject matter professional on properly designing and implementing Health IT solutions. In addition, the DM reviews current processes, recommends and incorporates new processes, works with all teams to support TeleTracking’s New Product Introduction (NPI) processes.

raw_data.title: Director of Software Engineering
raw_data.description: Director of Software Engineering leads the development and deployment of Health IT application projects according to the product roadmaps. Coordinates the evolution of technical designs and code components to support detailed specifications and functional/non-functional requirements. Participates directly in the creation of end-to-end architecture, technical designs, and code components for enterprise-scalable web applications. Ensures reusable code design, leveraging application architecture/framework capabilities and functionality. Facilitates and directly participate in code reviews.

raw_data.title: Director of Technical Support
raw_data.description: Director of Technical Support sets the strategy for Technical Support Center,  and ensures that the team has the resources and the abilities to support TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions and to resolve client technical issues in compliance with SLAs. Contributes to problem resolution as a key escalation point in client support process.

labor_categories.labor_category: Data Visualization and Business Intelligence Lead

raw_data.title: Data Visualization and Business Intelligence Lead
raw_data.description: The Data Visualization and Business Intelligence Lead creates  accurate dashboards and reports which highlight patterns and trends that drive changes to business processes and operational workflow changes. The Data Visualization and Business Intelligence Lead leverages analytics solutions built on TeleTracking’s Health IT platform.

raw_data.title: Integration Analyst (IA)
raw_data.description: The Integration Analyst (IA) is responsible for all efforts around the design, development, testing, support, and maintenance of TeleTracking application integration messaging infrastructure with other Health IT systems.  Through this work, the IA supports business processes for TeleTracking solutions and our clients. The position  implements HL7 messaging standards and structures and enterprise level interface integration platforms, and builds event based real-time interfaces. The IA role is also responsible for building integration solutions using RESTful Web Services, Object Oriented programming languages, and uses common algorithms and data structures, database concepts and design, and data access.

raw_data.title: Infrastructure Engineer 2 (IE2)
raw_data.description: Infrastructure Engineer 2 (IE2) plans, implements, and supports cloud platform network and infrastructure related resources for TeleTracking’s Health IT platform. Focuses on declarative automation deployment and configuration tools.

raw_data.title: Infrastructure Engineer 3 (IE3)
raw_data.description: Infrastructure Engineer 3 (IE3) plans, implements, and supports cloud platform network and infrastructure related resources for TeleTracking’s Health IT platform.  Drives automation and configuration best practices. Develops and maintains documentation of infrastructure and network behaviors. Performs infrastructure code reviews.  Collaborates with software engineers to ensure a scalable and secure infrastructure foundation.  Mentors IE 1 and IE 2s.

raw_data.title: Infrastructure Architect
raw_data.description: Infrastructure Architect contributes to technical architecture and design of complex Health IT systems, network topology (SDN), and CI/CD pipeline in support of the TeleTracking cloud platform.  Supports Principal Architect and other technical teams in deciding infrastructure and network strategy, technologies chosen, and future roadmap objectives.

raw_data.title: Lead Product Owner
raw_data.description: The Lead Product Owner leads a team of Product Owners while also supporting a Health IT product line. This role  leads the processes to ensure  the creation of complete user stories and acceptance criteria, and the prioritization of the feature/functionality backlog.

raw_data.title: Machine Learning Engineer 3 (MLE3)
raw_data.description: Machine Learning Engineer 3 (MLE3)  determines ways to use healthcare operations  data to automate key operational workflows and to inform customers of trends identified by the data.  The MLE 3 brings data together to answer business questions and drive change. The MLE 3 designs and develops machine learning algorithms that  provide insights for automating operational workflows in Health IT systems.

raw_data.title: Manager of Performance and Automation
raw_data.description: Manager of Performance and Automation is responsible for setting the direction and overall leadership of the performance and automation testing function supporting the development of TeleTracking’s Health IT platform. The manager determines the group’s priorities, work processes. The manager determines the tools and best practices and works with the team members to drive consistency and capability to increase the level of performance and automation testing expertise across the teams.

raw_data.title: Manager of Technical Support
raw_data.description: Manager of Technical Support manages a team of Technical Support Center employees in providing daily workflow direction, client satisfaction, support call responsiveness, quality case resolution, effective documentation, and departmental policy compliance. Coordinates technical training required to support TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions and assigns resources to support complex client requests and specialty queues.

raw_data.title: Outcomes Consultant (OC)
raw_data.description: The Outcomes Consultant (OC) leads the development and delivery of Health IT optimization engagements to our clients.  The OC engages with our clients to understand their operational processes and work environment and leads the optimization process to help ensure our clients are  achieving agreed upon outcomes.  The OC provides baseline metric analysis, benefit, and outcome estimates, and recommends improvement opportunities.

raw_data.title: Principal Architect
raw_data.description: Principal Architect advises the development team in areas of the technical architecture of Health IT applications and platforms. Coaches and provides hands-on support for Health IT solution design and problem solving. Creates end to end architecture, technical design, and code components for enterprise scalable web applications.  Participates in code reviews and on-going QA.

raw_data.title: Product Designer
raw_data.description: Product Designer creates multiple Health IT applications. Works with cross-functional stakeholders to  ensure compliance with TeleTracking product design standards.

raw_data.title: Product Owner
raw_data.description: The Product Owner defines user stories and acceptance criteria for Health IT solutions and supports the process of determining the prioritization of product backlogged items. This includes addressing  challenges and driving alignment across key stakeholders to, ensure the delivery of product updates across the feature backlog.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer 1 (SE1)
raw_data.description: Software Engineer 1 (SE1) writes, debugs, conducts unit testing and performance test code in select Health IT application layers, including front end (Web), middle layer (Web Services), and data access layer.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer 2 (SE2)
raw_data.description: Software Engineer 2 (SE2) writes, debugs, unit tests, and performance tests code in all Health IT application layers, including front end (Web), middle layer (Web Services), and data access layer. Utilizes domain driven techniques and design patterns to build and contribute to technical design.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer 3 (SE3)
raw_data.description: Software Engineer 3 (SE3) writes, debugs, performs unit tests and performance tests code in all Health IT application layers, including front end (Web), middle layer (Web Services), and data access layer and performs code reviews across all layers. Utilizes domain driven techniques and design patterns to build and contribute to technical design. Develops and maintains knowledge of implemented requirements and detailed application behaviors. Mentors SE 1s and SE 2s.

raw_data.title: Secucity Operations Engineer 1 (Sec Ops)
raw_data.description: Security Operations Engineer 1 (SecOps 1)  is responsible for security-related items for Production environments of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. Anticipates security breaches and recommends technologies to prevent data loss and service interruptions. Implements a capability driven and automated approach to TeleTracking’s  security operations, monitoring & detection, incident response, and  overall information security risk management.

raw_data.title: Software Engineering Manager (SEM)
raw_data.description: Software Engineering Manager (SEM) leads a software engineering team that creates the Health IT applications. This position has end-to-end technical ownership of a TeleTracking product including resource management and allocation and overall project management responsibilities.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer in Test (SET1)
raw_data.description: Software Engineer in Test (SET1) assists in creation and execution of tests derived from user stories. Uses testing techniques, both manual and automated, to identify , log, and verify defects across select components of TeleTracking’s Health IT platform.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer in Test (SET2)
raw_data.description: Software Engineer in Test (SET2) creates and executes  tests derived from user stories while leveraging SDLC. Uses testing techniques, both manual and automated, to identify , log, and verify defects across the entire TeleTracking’s Health IT platform.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer in Test (SET3)
raw_data.description: Software Engineer in Test (SET3) creates and executes  tests derived from user stories while leveraging SDLC. Uses testing techniques, both manual and automated, to identify , log, and verify defects across the entire TeleTracking’s Health IT platform. Mentor STE 1s and 2s.

raw_data.title: Senior Product Designer
raw_data.description: Senior Product Designer leads and manages the process for creating multiple Health IT applications across TeleTracking’s platform. Defines TeleTracking’s product design standards.

raw_data.title: Services Project Manager (SPM)
raw_data.description: The Services Project Manager (SPM) delivers TeleTracking solutions and serves as an adviser on Health IT delivery strategy to our clients. The SPM helps to ensure that project and change management standards are followed and leverages a strategic governance approach. The SPM uses tools and templates to effectively manage the project budget and helps ensure successful Health IT solution delivery.

raw_data.title: Technical Analyst (TA)
raw_data.description: The Technical Analyst (TA) builds the elements of Health IT solution design, collects key data attributes, and coordinates the integration of client specific data from other Health IT systems into our solutions. The Technical Analyst uses industry leading practices and client-specific workflow requirements to help ensure our solutions are properly configured.

raw_data.title: Director of Technical Operations (TechOps)
raw_data.description: Director of Technical Operations (TechOps) works cross-functionally within TeleTracking to help transform business and operations to enable delivery  of  cloud-based products. The Director is responsible for  the operations, automation, monitoring, and deployment activities of Health IT Software as a Service (SaaS) offerings.

raw_data.title: Technical Program Director
raw_data.description: Technical Program Director (TPD) oversees two or more of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. The Technical Program Director supports the collaboration with the commercial and technology teams to define new products and product features, creates ROI reviews and influences key stakeholders to align on product features and functionalities.

raw_data.title: Services Technical Project Manager (TPM)
raw_data.description: The Services Technical Project Manager (TPM) helps ensure that our clients’ technical environments are configured for optimal performance to assist our clients in realizing their intended outcomes. This role is responsible for all technical aspects of a Health IT project and requires coordination with our clients, other Health IT vendors, project team members, and TeleTracking’s software development.

raw_data.title: Engineering Technical Project Manager 1 (TPM1)
raw_data.description: Engineering Technical Project Manager 1 (TPM1) manages single project end-to-end from planning to delivery and commercialization of Health IT solutions.  Assesses and communicates risks, milestones, dependencies, and status to internal and external teams at all levels.  Manages change control, scoping, and contingency planning.

raw_data.title: Engineering Technical Project Manager 3 (TPM3)
raw_data.description: Engineering Technical Project Manager 3 (TPM3) manages multiple projects end-to-end from planning to delivery and commercialization of Health IT solutions. Assesses and communicates risks, milestones, dependencies, and status to internal and external teams at all levels.  Manages change control, scoping, and contingency planning.

raw_data.title: Technical Program Manager
raw_data.description: Technical Program Manager supports the definition and ongoing priorities of one or more of TeleTracking’s Health IT solutions. The Technical Program Manager works with others to define new products and product features, conducts technical presentations and works directly with key stakeholders to define priorities and product requirements.

raw_data.title: Technical Support Engineer 1 (TSE1)
raw_data.description: Technical Support Engineer 1 (TSE1) supports and troubleshoots select TeleTracking Health IT solutions. Identifies root cause of training, process, or product-related issues and recommends solutions. Leverages internal tools for issue escalation, management, and resolution.

raw_data.title: Technical Support Engineer 2  (TSE2)
raw_data.description: Technical Support Engineer 2 (TSE2) supports and troubleshoots multiple TeleTracking Health IT solutions. Identifies root cause of training, process, or product-related issues and recommends solutions. Leverages internal tools for issue escalation, management, and resolution. Coach and mentor TSE 1s.

raw_data.title: Technical Support Engineer 3 (TSE3)
raw_data.description: Technical Support Engineer 3 (TSE3) supports and troubleshoots all TeleTracking Health IT solutions. Identifies root cause of training, process, or product-related issues and recommend solutions. Leverages internal tools for issue escalation, management, and resolution. Participates in the issue resolution lifecycle process with development and quality assurance. Coach and mentor TSE 1s and 2s.

raw_data.title: Technical Support Engineer 4 (TSE4)
raw_data.description: Technical Support Engineer 4 (TSE4) is a subject matter professional who provides support and guidance to Technical Support Engineer 3s, 2s, and 1s. Handles client escalations involving multiple technical issues including onsite client-specific issues. Is a liaison between Technical Support and the Development/QA team regarding new and existing TeleTracking Health IT solutions to identify common support issues or trends. Mentors and guides junior technicians.

raw_data.title: User Content Developer 3
raw_data.description: The User Content Developer 3 works with engineers, product managers, platform quality, product owners, and client services to make TeleTracking’s Health IT applications easier to use.

raw_data.title: Workflow Consultant (WFC)
raw_data.description: The Workflow Consultant (WFC) is an experienced team member within TeleTracking, responsible for developing operational workflows, and configuring our Health IT solutions to enable clients to best leverage TeleTracking’s leading practices.
